               <msContents>
                  <summary change="#ai-catalogue">
                     <p>الصحيفة الكاملة.</p>
                     <p>A collection of prayers and doxologies ascribed to the Fourth Imam of the <lb/>Shi'a, 'Ali ibnu'l-Husayn commonly called Zaynu'l-'Abidin. See Brockelmann, <lb/>vol. 1, p. 44; and Ahlwardt's Berlin Arabic Catalogue, vol. III, pp. 376-377 <lb/>Nos. 3769-70, where the book is fully described.</p>
                     <p>This MS, belonged to my former colleague Shaykh Hasan of Tabriz, who gave <lb/>it to me when he left Cambridge in June, 1911. It contains 194 ff. of 13'5 x 7'5 C. <lb/>and 11 l., is written in an excellent modern Persian naskh, fully pointed, with</p>
                     <p>rubrications, and was transcribed by Muḥammad Amin of Na'in, who completed it <lb/>on 11 Sha'bán, 1087/20 October, 1676. In the second colophon on f. 193 the <lb/>alternative title of Zubiru Ali Muhammad wa-Injilu Ahli l-Bayt is given. The <lb/>text is divided into two parts at f. 176. The first part ends, like the Berlin MS. <lb/>No. 3769, with the prayer for the dispersal of sorrows, at the end of which is <lb/>written:</p>
                     <p>The succeeding portion is entitled (f. 176'):</p>
                     <p>الصحيفة وكان من تسبيحه اعنى زين العابدين عليه السلام</p>
                     <p>تمت الصحيفة الشريفة الكاملة بعون الله وتوفيقه</p>
                     <p>ومنا الحق ببعض نسخ</p>
                     <p>نقل من حط الشيخ الشهيد رحمه الله صح</p>
                     <p>Opposite this in the margin, also written in red, are the words:</p>
                     <p>العين في مشهد الحسين <lb/>نور العين في</p>
                  </summary>
